22.\", \"from\": 1919, \"to\": 2053, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Van Niekerk's career\", \"from\": 1919, \"to\": 1939}, {\"ngram\": \"the 200m distance\", \"from\": 1950, \"to\": 1967}, {\"ngram\": \"19.82 set\", \"from\": 2035, \"to\": 2044}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Richardson's best 200m time is 19.99, the same as Maswanganyi.\", \"from\": 2055, \"to\": 2117, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2055, \"end\": 2065, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Samuel_Richardson\", \"score\": 0.9999376914733462, \"rank\": 6.231233669389784e-05, \"text\": \"Richardson\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q36180\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Samuel_Richardson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Samuel_Richardson\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Maswanganyi\", \"from\": 2105, \"to\": 2116}]}, {\"sentence\": \"No fewer than 17 different athletes have run under 20-seconds this year alone - and seven of them have posted sub-19.90 times.\", \"from\": 2119, \"to\": 2245, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"No fewer than 17 different athletes\", \"from\": 2119, \"to\": 2154}, {\"ngram\": \"20-seconds\", \"from\": 2170, \"to\": 2180}, {\"ngram\": \"sub-19.90 times\", \"from\": 2229, \"to\": 2244}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Jamaica'sUsain Boltholds the 200m world record of 19.19 which he set in Berlin in 2009.\", \"from\": 2247, \"to\": 2334, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2247, \"end\": 2254, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jamaica\", \"score\": 0.9999911285388112, \"rank\": 8.865951628489677e-06, \"text\": \"Jamaica\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jamaica\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jamaica\"}, {\"begin\": 2319, \"end\": 2325, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Berlin\", \"score\": 0.9971921884087246, \"rank\": 0.0027897436701403203, \"text\": \"Berlin\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Berlin\", \"dbp